1
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:57,960
We haven't had anything for two days now, All-New.

2
00:00:57,960 --> 00:00:58,800
I'm starting to get hungry.

3
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,320
I don't know what kind of mushroom this is,
but it looks damn delicious.

4
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,080
A bear!

5
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:08,800
It’s like the nature on this island...

6
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:09,800
is absolutely furious with us.

7
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:12,520
Oh, this is really happening.

8
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:14,560
I think the best solution for everyone...

9
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:16,880
is that we need to get off this island as fast as possible.

10
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:18,640
Kree!

11
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:20,160
Calm down, Mushroom-Eared Bear, okay?

12
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:23,400
Wait, this is Tik Jes!

13
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:41,240
KREE WITH A MUSTACHE

14
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:44,280
I think we should just
grill the mushrooms and eat them.

15
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:46,240
We haven't had anything
for two days now, All-New.

16
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:47,560
No!

17
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:49,720
I've already opened my Chakra
to communicate with this mushroom.

18
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:51,440
Its energy is really weird.

19
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:52,720
And besides, if you eat it...

20
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:54,360
it'll cause hallucinations.
It'll make things even worse.

21
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:57,080
But I'm starving.
I told you to give me the mushroom, All-New!

22
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:59,440
Can't you just be patient?

23
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:01,640
Just think of it as a water fast,
you know?

24
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,000
Fasting for three days.

25
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,560
I'm not taking this anymore.
I'm going to eat it right now, All-New!

26
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,160
Give me the mushroom!

27
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,840
I told you to...

28
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:08,840
stop...

29
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:11,200
acting like a baby!

30
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,720
Oh! My mushroom!

31
00:02:15,720 --> 00:02:18,440
You guys, build a massive fire!

32
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:19,960
We caught a fish!

33
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:26,040
I think it's cooked.
We can probably eat it now.

34
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:28,640
I was the first one to spot this fish!

35
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,560
I get to eat the belly, okay?
I called it first!

36
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:33,160
You only spotted it.
I was the first one to dive in and catch it!

37
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:34,840
So I should get the belly.

38
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:37,720
Hey, but I was the first one to carry it.
I used the most energy.

39
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:38,800
I'll take the middle part.

40
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,240
I helped carry it too,
you know.

41
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,960
So I get to
eat the belly part as well!

42
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:44,080
Oh, please, Chaba, bitch.

43
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:46,920
You didn't put in a single ounce
of effort when they were lifting it.

44
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:48,360
Acting like you get to choose what to eat.

45
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,760
Go eat the fish eyes over there!

46
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,120
True.

47
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,240
The meat around the fish head...

48
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,760
I can share that with you, Chaba.

49
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:55,200
Thank you, Kree.

50
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:58,320
In that case,
I'll sacrifice myself and just eat the tail.

51
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,640
The tail barely has any meat, man.

52
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,880
But you chose it already, so...

53
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:09,360
Sky, does your piece of the fish
even have meat?

54
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:12,360
I've been gnawing on this
until my teeth are loose, and I don't see any meat at all.

55
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,360
Right? What kind of shitty fish is this?

56
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,000
I bite into it and there's no meat,
only skin.

57
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,120
What kind of fish belly is this?
There's no meat either.

58
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,920
How could it have meat?

59
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:23,000
The fish you guys caught
is an Angel-bush fish.

60
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,960
It only has meat in the tail.

61
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:28,040
What the hell?
If you knew, why didn't you tell us?

62
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:30,320
Well, you guys were just being stupid.

63
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,760
You were planning to keep
the fish all to yourself, weren't you?

64
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:34,240
Did you just call me stupid?

65
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,120
You, nerd!

66
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:37,640
Everyone!

67
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:42,080
Everyone, stop!

68
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,360
Be quiet now!

69
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:49,920
What kind of crew members are you?
You're tearing each other apart.

70
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,280
Mr. All-New, bring that fish over here.

71
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:57,080
Bring it here.
Let's divide it equally.

72
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,280
Here.

73
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,400
Thank you.

74
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:03,320
Enjoy your meal, everyone.

75
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:04,560
But it's such a shame, you know.

76
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,320
That we only have a cap gun.

77
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:08,240
If it were a real gun...

78
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,960
we could probably hunt
so many animals.

79
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:12,080
We don't need a real gun to hunt.

80
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:14,280
Because I have already invented this!

81
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:16,440
Tada!

82
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,920
Ms. Petchgam Ploy,
why did you bring a Chakhe?

83
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:22,720
It's a bow!

84
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,720
Oh.

85
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:26,080
I am going to teach
all of you how to hunt myself.

86
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:35,560
This bird is your food.

87
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,160
Actually, I'm a seagan.

88
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:38,320
What the hell is a seagan?

89
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:42,160
It's like being a vegan,
but you can only eat seafood.

90
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:44,040
I have prepared a cast net for you.

91
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,840
If you want to eat,
you go down and catch it yourself.

92
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:47,720
Here, take the net with you.

93
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,480
And...

94
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,880
what do you want me to do?

95
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:01,400
You don't have to do anything.
Just stand there and look handsome.

96
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:02,760
Huh?

97
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,760
So you just want me to stand here and wait?

98
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:09,320
Stand here and wait?

99
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,560
KREE WITH A MUSTACHE

100
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:13,720
No.

101
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:16,400
Just stand there and look handsome like that.

102
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:19,760
Because you look so good
with that mustache.

103
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:20,720
I look cool, right?

104
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,000
Absolutely.

105
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,480
Man, I wish I had a mirror
to look at myself.

106
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,960
Wow, a match made in heaven.

107
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:37,680
One loves to compliment,
and the other loves to be flattered.

108
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:41,240
Mr. Chai, Mr. All-New,
what are you guys just standing around for?

109
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,840
Go find some fish already!

110
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:51,440
I called dibs
on the seaweed soup today, alright?

111
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,440
Seaweed is covering my feet!

112
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,280
Keep it down, please.
Little Kree is sleeping.

113
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:00,560
Little Kree?

114
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,080
Ms. Petchgam Ploy,
let me ask you straight.

115
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:03,720
You aren't high on something,
are you?

116
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,800
You two did a wonderful job,
you know.

117
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:09,520
Surviving those piranhas in the ocean...

118
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,840
I knew it!
It was a piranha!

119
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:12,840
No wonder it was so vicious.

120
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:13,760
Exactly.

121
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,600
You already knew there were piranhas...

122
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:17,840
but you still made us
go down and catch fish in the ocean?

123
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:19,760
But you survived, didn't you?
See?

124
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:23,680
Every single day,
with a bit of courage and a little bit of stupidity...

125
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:26,000
it makes the two of you stronger.

126
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,000
I'm proud of you.

127
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:30,800
It's nothing.

128
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:33,520
I think, honestly...

129
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:35,920
we should make Little Kree...

130
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,680
sleep comfortably, don't you think?

131
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,520
Mr. Chai!

132
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:45,160
Get out, both of you!
Go eat your piranhas or whatever!

133
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:46,200
Get out!

134
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:49,960
Oh, you're alright, Little Kree.

135
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:59,520
Hey, Chaba, help pitch the tent
before you sleep!

136
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,880
This girl is utterly useless.

137
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:04,000
In that case,
while Gift and I are sleeping...

138
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,240
you stand guard.

139
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,800
Fine, I can sleep standing up anyway.
What about it?

140
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,400
No, you can't just sleep standing up.

141
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:11,160
You have to slap mosquitoes
for us while we're asleep too, honey.

142
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:12,960
I'm starting to get hungry.

143
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:13,720
Yeah.

144
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:16,080
Go check on the guys
and see what they found for us to eat.

145
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,320
Me? Check on the guys?

146
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,320
Yeah, go already!

147
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,120
Are you sure you want me to go?

148
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:19,960
Just go!

149
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:20,880
Don't regret it later.

150
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:21,640
I'll slap you!

151
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:22,640
I'll be right back then.

152
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,680
What should we use as a pillow?

153
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,440
An inflatable life jacket
might work, you know.

154
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:28,120
Yeah, that works.

155
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,400
What about a blanket then?

156
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:31,160
Good question.

157
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:36,720
Or should I just have Chai
hold me while we sleep? He has broad shoulders.

158
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,600
Don't tell me that you and Chai...

159
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,600
have hooked up...

160
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,800
Are you crazy?
That is so gross!

161
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:49,440
Hey, you guys!

162
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:50,560
I had the longest run.

163
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,920
Ms. Petchgam Ploy is calling
an urgent meeting right now!

164
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:57,600
Come on, everyone!
Let's do some exercise to relax.

165
00:07:57,600 --> 00:08:00,240
It's just a short, little class.
Everyone, follow my lead.

166
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,880
This is yoga.

167
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:05,320
Practice inhaling and exhaling.
This is Child's Pose!

168
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,360
Kree!

169
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,240
Get back here!

170
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,440
Don't do it.

171
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:14,000
What?

172
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,880
I'm doing this
because I want to help all of you.

173
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:16,880
Don't be stressed.

174
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,120
Don't be stressed.

175
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,440
Do as I say.

176
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,800
So?

177
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,760
I told you to do it!

178
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,720
No, I won't do it.

179
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,120
I'm not letting you
boss us around anymore.

180
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:27,800
What?

181
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,520
Yeah! Who are you?
Why do we have to follow your orders?

182
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,720
Whose fault is it that
we're suffering like this anyway?

183
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:33,280
Yeah!

184
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:33,880
It's because of you!

185
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:35,000
Yeah!

186
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,600
And more importantly...

187
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:41,320
On this island, there is no such thing
as supervisor and employees.

188
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,480
That's right!

189
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,480
We're all equal here.

190
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:47,400
And on this island,
nobody takes orders from anyone else.

191
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:49,000
You love giving orders so much?
Let me try then!

192
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,080
Petch, bitch,
go find some water for me to drink!

193
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,240
Petch, bitch,
go find some food for me to eat!

194
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:57,640
Petch, bitch,
go get some water to wash my feet!

195
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,440
Petch, bitch,
come massage my feet!

196
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:00,960
Yeah!

197
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:01,960
I'm sore.

198
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:03,160
Just by the name alone...

199
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:04,480
you can tell she's poor.

200
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,080
Chaba!

201
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,640
Go build a house for me to live in!

202
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:07,800
Go!

203
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:08,760
Take your mat with you, Petch, bitch!

204
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:09,840
Go!

205
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:11,040
Petch, bitch!
Petch, bitch!

206
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:11,680
Go!

207
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:12,880
Go, go, go!

208
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:13,400
Petch, bitch!
Petch, bitch!

209
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,160
Go!

210
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:15,000
Get out, Petch, bitch!

211
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,120
Just go!

212
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,400
Petch, bitch, get out!
Get out!

213
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,040
Fabulous!

214
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:18,720
Fabulous, right?

215
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,520
We are like the villains here.

216
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:22,720
Nobody wants Petch around anyway.

217
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,920
What is it, Kree?

218
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:24,600
Where are you going?

219
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:30,920
When is this
ever going to be full?

220
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:33,000
I have to apologize
on behalf of the others...

221
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,320
for calling you...

222
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,840
Petch, bitch.

223
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,120
That was way too harsh.

224
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,000
It really was.

225
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,320
And it's especially harsh
that you just repeated it.

226
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,120
I'm sorry.

227
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:47,200
Forget it.
There's no need to apologize.

228
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:51,200
I'm the reason why
everyone is stranded on this island.

229
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:53,880
But it was an accident.
You didn't mean for it to happen.

230
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,240
Ms. Petchgam Ploy...

231
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:03,680
You haven't eaten anything at all,
have you?

232
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:11,720
I noticed that
when you were dividing the first fish...

233
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:15,680
you were the only one who didn't eat.

234
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:20,640
That's right.

235
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:25,120
I just...I feel so guilty.

236
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:29,920
So I wanted to take care of you,
take care of all of you...

237
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:32,040
and make sure
you were well-fed and comfortable.

238
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:34,280
But that's too much, don't you think?

239
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,920
Especially since you
haven't eaten anything for days.

240
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:37,720
I did eat.

241
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:40,840
I already ate the mushrooms
on this island.

242
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,600
The mushrooms?

243
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,680
You mean these white mushrooms right here?

244
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:44,520
Yes.

245
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:45,600
You can't do that!

246
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:48,760
All-New said these mushrooms
are extremely dangerous.

247
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:50,720
Plus, eating them causes hallucinations!

248
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:51,800
Really?

249
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:57,320
Oh, no wonder.
I felt like I couldn't control myself at all.

250
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,440
That explains it.

251
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:04,640
No wonder Ms. Petchgam Ploy
has been acting so strange.

252
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:05,560
But this is actually great...

253
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:07,520
it gives me a chance
to get closer to her.

254
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,520
I'll just play along for now.

255
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:15,360
Why is your skin...
so beautiful?

256
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,440
So glowing and radiant.

257
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:20,440
Hasn't it been damaged
by the sun here at all?

258
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,360
The sun?

259
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:24,920
Oh, right, the sun.
The sun is incredibly strong here.

260
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,520
But I'm not afraid.

261
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,120
Because...

262
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,080
Tada!

263
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:31,880
I'm so lucky I always carry
my instant-glow sunscreen with me.

264
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:35,200
Because it has SPF 50+ PA++++.

265
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,200
Let me apply a bit more.

266
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,080
So cute.

267
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,000
And most importantly,
it doesn't leave any white cast after applying.

268
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,320
It's waterproof and sweatproof too.

269
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:54,920
I could listen to you talk all day.

270
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:57,640
If I talked all day,
I'd probably be crazy.

271
00:11:57,640 --> 00:12:00,240
Let's hurry up.
Otherwise, they're going scold us again.

272
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:01,320
Let's go bring some water to our friends.

273
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,680
They're literally calling me
Petch, bitch, now.

274
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:10,600
Hey, you guys.

275
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,760
Do you think we're going
to be stranded on this island...

276
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:14,200
to the point...

277
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,920
where we'll have to kill each other for meat?

278
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:17,000
It's definitely possible.

279
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:20,840
But right now,
I already know who we should kill first.

280
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:21,920
I have someone in mind.

281
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:22,840
I do too.

282
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:23,960
Don't tell me...

283
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,720
Petchgam Ploy.

284
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:28,360
Yeah, I've been noticing it for a while now.

285
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:30,600
There's definitely something
going on between her and Kree.

286
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:33,840
She works us to the bone
looking for food just to pamper Kree?

287
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:35,000
Yeah!

288
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:39,040
That woman literally
said out loud that Kree is charming...

289
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,840
and irresistible with that mustache.

290
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,280
Well, Petchgam Ploy...

291
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:46,520
being infatuated with Kree's mustache
is one weird thing...

292
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:49,760
but All-New calling Petchgam Ploy
"that woman" like that?

293
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:51,000
Now that's a whole new level.

294
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:55,440
Oh please, you literally
called her "Petch, bitch" and I didn't say a single word!

295
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,640
"Fabulous!", "Incredible!"

296
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:58,880
Alright, All-New.

297
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,960
Since when did you start
gossiping like that?

298
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:01,960
Is this...

299
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,800
Is this too harsh?

300
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:06,120
I was just trash-talking
along with you guys.

301
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,440
I think he was probably
just suppressing his feelings.

302
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:12,280
Coming back from hunting only
to find Kree snuggling up against Ms. Petch...

303
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,520
Did you say "just" suppressing his feelings?

304
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:17,760
Yeah, just...

305
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:21,880
I think at this very moment,
whoever has a grudge against Petchgam Ploy...

306
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:25,800
it's time for us to get our revenge.

307
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:28,880
True! Should we order her
to go hunt wild boars for us to eat?

308
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,240
Yeah, great idea!

309
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,840
Or...

310
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:34,200
Should we make her
clean up our poop and pee?

311
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,320
Great!

312
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:38,200
Wash our feet,
and then use that water to wash Sky’s face?

313
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:39,160
How about that?

314
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:40,040
Great!

315
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:41,120
No, that's not great!
That's not great!

316
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:41,680
It's not great?

317
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:43,920
No! Are you crazy?
Washing my face with feet water!

318
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,400
I thought it was a good idea.

319
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,960
What kind of mushroom is this?
It looks damn delicious. It's huge!

320
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:48,600
Is it a bit too big?

321
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,000
Hey, don't!

322
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,200
Look right here!

323
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,120
I have lots of shrimps here
and you won't eat them?

324
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:55,400
That's true.

325
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,400
I don't want to eat them anymore.
I'm bored. We eat them every single day.

326
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:03,000
Aren't you bored? Eat this instead.
Give me the mushroom, I'm going to eat it.

327
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:11,800
A ghost or an animal?

328
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:13,280
An animal.

329
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,560
Big or small?

330
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:15,440
Big.

331
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:16,400
Like, very big?

332
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:17,720
Very big!

333
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:29,040
One, two...

334
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:38,320
I'm hurt!
I can't run anymore!

335
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:40,200
Where am I going
to hide from the bear?

336
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,400
I'll just play dead.

337
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:54,880
Stinky! She probably
hasn't brushed her teeth in days.

338
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,360
Rotten stinky like this,
she must really be dead.

339
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:11,360
What do we do?
Where do we go?

340
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:13,200
Let's hide behind this peach tree first!
Come on!

341
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,520
Is this it? Right here?

342
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:16,080
Get our bodies closer together!

343
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:30,800
Hey, your body is pressed
right against mine like this...

344
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,520
don't you feel anything at all?

345
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:33,520
Of course, I do.

346
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:36,440
I'm terrified of dying!

347
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:42,320
Well, if you're terrified of dying,
don't you think it'd be easier if we just stood back-to-back?

348
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,400
Oh, right.

349
00:15:56,400 --> 00:16:00,600
I'm definitely not making it out alive, Chai.

350
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,600
Me neither.

351
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,680
These aren't the ones
who pulled the mushroom!

352
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:10,320
Here.

353
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,840
Give me the mushroom,
I'm going to eat it.

354
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:16,480
You're a dead meat!

355
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:22,720
Look, All-New!
The penis-shaped amulet mushroom! This is our weapon!

356
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:26,000
Sky.

357
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:28,160
Let's not do this.

358
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:30,760
It's like the nature on this island...
is absolutely furious with us.

359
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:32,080
You, moron!

360
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,360
Why are you trying
to save the planet right now?

361
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,520
We're about to die!

362
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:35,480
For real, man!

363
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:37,720
Don't make things any worse
than they already are!

364
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:38,720
He's here!

365
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:47,200
Are you really going to bite
a flight attendant like me?

366
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:54,720
All-New!

367
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:56,200
What's wrong with the bear?

368
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:58,200
I don't know
but why does he look so sad?

369
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:08,600
He loves me...the bear loves...

370
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:12,440
Why the hell did you slap me?

371
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:15,720
Mr. Bear! Mr. Bear!

372
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:24,040
Oh, this is really happening.

373
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:26,360
My face is full of holes now!

374
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:39,160
Someone like you won't die that easily, Sky.
I'm here to help!

375
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:40,160
Ms. Petchgam Ploy!

376
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,440
Help me, please!

377
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:46,320
I'm so glad you aren't calling me
Petch, bitch, anymore.

378
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:49,080
Why did the bear freeze up like that?

379
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:52,400
Because I shot my arrow
to paralyze him for a moment.

380
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:54,320
It's an acupressure shot
to block the bear's pressure points.

381
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:56,640
What are you waiting for?
Kill him already!

382
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:58,360
No!

383
00:17:58,360 --> 00:17:59,880
We're the ones invading his home!

384
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:02,120
What did he even do wrong?
And you still want to kill him?

385
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:05,120
If we don't kill him,
he's definitely going to kill us!

386
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:09,160
I think the best solution for everyone...

387
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:11,160
is that we need to get off
this island as fast as possible.

388
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:13,880
Chai, Tid-Gift!

389
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:14,840
Hey.

390
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:15,840
Untie us, would you?

391
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:19,800
How did you even survive?

392
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,040
I thought the bear ate you already.

393
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:22,560
The bear couldn't find me, that's why.

394
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:27,720
A bear!

395
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:31,200
Mr. Kreetha...

396
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:33,800
if we're still here,
we won't make it out alive.

397
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,120
We need to escape.

398
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,120
How can we escape though?

399
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:43,440
Here, we're lucky.

400
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:44,760
I've found a liferaft there.

401
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:50,000
But would that liferaft
big enough for all of us?

402
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,560
Well, it's better than being eaten by a bear.

403
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,040
Why is the ground shaking?

404
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:58,480
Hey, Chai!

405
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:01,120
Is this an earthquake?

406
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:05,360
It's an earthquake!

407
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:06,640
Help!

408
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:08,440
Watch out, watch out!

409
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:10,440
We're gonna die!

410
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,640
What the hell is wrong with this island?

411
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:17,280
Is it trying to kill us or what?

412
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:20,200
Everyone, let's hurry up
and gather at the liferaft.

413
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,200
Oh...

414
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:25,680
The earthquake might stop...

415
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:27,680
but our lives are the ones
that won't be able to go on.

416
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:33,560
Ms. Sky, Mr. All-New, run away!
I'll handle this myself!

417
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:38,320
Let's fight!

418
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:42,720
I can't hold it off much longer!

419
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:43,720
Ms. Petchgam Ploy!

420
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:48,680
Kree!

421
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:56,880
Calm down,
Mushroom-Eared Bear, okay?

422
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,080
A Mushroom-Eared Bear...

423
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:10,600
I missed you so much, my dear friend.
It's been so long since we last met.

424
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,600
Wait, this is Tik Jes!

425
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:16,320
Don't tell me...

426
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:19,480
are you here shooting the show, Navigator?

427
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:22,960
These people trespassed
and harmed the living Bear-Eared Mushrooms.

428
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,600
I told them to stop but they wouldn't listen.

429
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:26,560
Ah, I see, I see.

430
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:28,520
I'll communicate with everyone
so they understand.

431
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:29,920
What language is he
even speaking with the bear?

432
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:31,520
How can they understand each other?

433
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:33,320
Tik language.

434
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:38,120
Tik, sir!

435
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:39,160
May I please shake your hand?

436
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:40,520
I'm a huge fan of yours!

437
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:41,720
Especially your environmental conservation work.

438
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:43,040
I mean, I really like you!

439
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:48,920
Hello everyone.
I'm Tik, the Navigator.

440
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:51,760
I'd like to ask for permission to act
as the representative to communicate...

441
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:53,880
between the Mushroom-Eared Bear
and everyone here.

442
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:54,720
Of course!

443
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:57,320
Whatever you want to do,
I'm okay with it all.

444
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:00,560
It's like this.
The Mushroom-Eared Bear is extremely angry...

445
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:03,320
that you guys picked the Bear-Eared Mushrooms
on the Bear-Mushroom-Ear Island...

446
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:04,760
and even trespassed into his private territory...

447
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:07,360
which is the Mushroom-Ear-Bear Beach.

448
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:10,240
Let me double-check this real quick.

449
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:12,080
The bear is named
"Mushroom-Eared Bear."

450
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:14,400
The mushroom is named
"Bear-Eared Mushroom."

451
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:17,760
And the island is named
"Bear-Mushroom-Ear Island." Is that correct?

452
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:19,760
That is correct, young lady.

453
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,920
The reason the Mushroom-Eared Bear is so angry...

454
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:26,720
is because he's afraid that
you guys are going to destroy his nature.

455
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:27,400
Oh.

456
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,920
But I already told him that
you guys are the disaster victims...

457
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:32,400
and didn't have any malicious intentions.

458
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:35,680
Tik, by the way,
why is the bear named Mushroom-Eared Bear?

459
00:21:35,680 --> 00:21:38,600
Because the mushrooms and the bears
on this island belong to the same family.

460
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:39,960
It might sound a bit strange...

461
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:41,440
but scientific evidence shows that...

462
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,360
Mr. Mushroom-Eared Bear here...

463
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:43,520
has evolved from mushrooms.

464
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:45,320
Therefore, he is a mushroom-species bear...

465
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:48,080
and his name is Mushroom-Eared Bear.

466
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:50,080
Oh! Ah, right.

467
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:55,240
Wow, there are so many things
in this world that we still don't know about.

468
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:56,360
I used to wonder...

469
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:59,360
that the person who gave birth to me
might actually be a rock.

470
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:00,880
Or maybe a tree.

471
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:02,680
That is correct.

472
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:07,440
There are still many things
that you might have never known before.

473
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:09,280
Are you ready to embark on the journey?

474
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:12,280
If you're ready, let's go together with...

475
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:14,920
the Navigator!

476
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:16,720
Let's go!

477
00:22:16,720 --> 00:22:19,040
Hey, wait, wait, wait!

478
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,440
We really want to go with you too...

479
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:22,920
but right now, we are stranded on this island.

480
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:25,240
So could you please help tell Mr. Bear...

481
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:27,520
that we'd like to stay on this island
for just a little bit...

482
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:29,640
until we can find a way
to get back home as soon as possible?

483
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:30,520
Of course.

484
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:33,520
I'll help build a boat
for everyone to go home.

485
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:36,080
Oh, that's fabulous!

486
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:39,800
Tik Jes!

487
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:43,400
I'm not sick
and having hallucinations right now, right?

488
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:46,880
It might not be hallucinations
but it could be infatuation...

489
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:52,800
Wait a minute, Chaba.

490
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,280
Where the hell have you been?

491
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:55,880
I was running away from the bear.

492
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:57,720
They say if you're running away from a bear,
you should play dead.

493
00:22:57,720 --> 00:23:00,000
So I played dead,
but then I actually fell asleep.

494
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:04,960
The bear fell for it,
and once he believed it, I fell into a deep sleep.

495
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:06,800
You know, we are completely freaking out right now...

496
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:09,000
but I have good news to tell everyone!

497
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:09,520
What?

498
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:10,480
What is it?

499
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:11,680
What's the news, Chaba?

500
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:14,360
A chopper is coming to pick us up
and take us home!

501
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:22,320
Really?
And who did you contact to pick us up, Chaba?

502
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:23,360
Doctor Yep!

503
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:26,000
He wants me to do a live stream
selling creams for his clinic.

504
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:29,440
Tomorrow morning, he's sending a chopper
to pick me up and take me home.

505
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,400
We're going home!

506
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,160
Wait a minute, Chaba.

507
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:36,640
There's no phone signal here at all.

508
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:38,000
How did you manage to contact him?

509
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:40,080
Well, it's because of Doctor Yep's
sheer psycho nature.

510
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:42,240
He put a GPS tracker on me.

511
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,720
Right here.

512
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:46,160
He was afraid that I wouldn't go back
to do the live stream sales for him.

513
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,120
But it turns out to be a good thing.

514
00:23:47,120 --> 00:23:49,280
His psycho behavior is getting us back home.

515
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:51,440
Otherwise, we'd definitely be screwed.

516
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:55,920
In that case,
shouldn't we go get some rest first?

517
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:57,280
Sounds good.

518
00:23:57,280 --> 00:23:58,520
Everyone has been exhausted enough.

519
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:00,960
That's wonderful.

520
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:04,080
Because my body needs a bed...

521
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:06,080
and the person I need beside me is you.

522
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:10,760
Was it me or you
who let my heart slip away?

523
00:24:12,080 --> 00:24:13,720
Okay, let's go.
Come on, Mr. Bear.

524
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,560
Hey, wait, no.

525
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:18,120
No?

526
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:19,120
Mr. Bear, let's go.

527
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,840
The bear gets to go...

528
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:23,600
but I don't get to go.

529
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,280
I'll just stay right here.

530
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:32,640
We gather here together,

531
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:37,920
Hand in hand,
united in heart.

532
00:24:37,920 --> 00:24:41,680
All friends,
joyful and cheerful,

533
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:47,320
Happy every one of us.

534
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:51,000
Unity,

535
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,480
That is one heart,

536
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:56,880
supreme and beautiful.

537
00:24:59,160 --> 00:25:00,640
Wait a minute, Mr. Bear,

538
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:04,600
if you can sing this well,
why don't you just speak human language?

539
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:05,960
No, he can't.

540
00:25:05,960 --> 00:25:08,960
This is the only human song
that Mr. Bear can sing.

541
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:16,960
Hey!

542
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,640
The chopper is here!

543
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:23,280
But it's so tiny,
will we all even fit?

544
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:25,600
What do we do?

545
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:27,960
I forgot to think about the space!

546
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:31,760
I guess only one person
can go home with me.

547
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:32,800
Hey! Hey!

548
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:33,920
Think, people!

549
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:35,200
I'll give up my spot.

550
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:38,040
I'll stay and look after those
who are still stuck on the island.

551
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,280
Think of a solution!

552
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:43,280
Chaba, I want to go home,
can you take me home?

553
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:47,560
Chaba, I love you!

554
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:49,640
Love doesn't put food on the table.

555
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:50,360
You stay here.

556
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:52,920
Back when we were building a tent,
what did you call me?

557
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:54,280
You said I was useless.

558
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:03,280
The real hero has arrived.

559
00:26:03,280 --> 00:26:04,720
Ms. Chaba.

560
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:06,400
Let's go home together.

561
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:07,960
My little money-maker.

562
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:10,400
Just "money-maker" is enough, doctor.

563
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,320
Doctor,

564
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:13,680
how many seats are in this chopper?

565
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:17,240
Well, just you and me.
Two seats, that's it.

566
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:18,200
Oh.

567
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:20,600
Hey, wait, wait, wait!

568
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:24,600
This is perfect,
it fits exactly two people.

569
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:26,440
Everyone, don't worry.

570
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:28,880
Because I've brought medicines...

571
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:30,800
for everyone who
has to stay on the island.

572
00:26:30,800 --> 00:26:34,040
Plus, there's a full set of
skincare products from Yeppy Clinic!

573
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:35,640
Don't worry at all!

574
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:36,760
Oh my, wow, so much stuff!

575
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:37,760
Is this one good?

576
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:38,760
There!

577
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,280
Tik, you know how to fly a chopper, right?

578
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,520
Of course, I do.

579
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:45,760
That's perfect, Tik.

580
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:48,800
We get to go home,
just the two of us.

581
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:52,680
Chaba, bitch,
how could you do this to me? You traitor!

582
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:55,520
Well, I'm going back to do the live stream
for your 7/7 mega sale, aren't I?

583
00:26:55,520 --> 00:26:59,160
And I want Tik to sit there
and watch me sell so I feel motivated.

584
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:01,680
Do you expect me to go back
and sell while looking at your face?

585
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:05,240
Nice to meet you all!

586
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:07,000
See ya!

587
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,000
Mr. Bear..

588
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:12,880
Let's go, Tik.

589
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:13,720
Ready to embark on the journal...

590
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:15,040
Journey!

591
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:19,800
I'll hit your head with a coconut!

592
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:23,560
That Chaba,

593
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:24,960
What a traitor!

594
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:26,160
Flying away,

595
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:27,600
probably swooning over...

596
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:29,880
Tik Jes.

597
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:33,280
Under the scorching sun,
I stand lonely,

598
00:27:33,280 --> 00:27:35,120
Burning within.

599
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:40,200
Like a sword slicing through my heart,
leaving it shattered.

600
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,200
Who are you talking to?

601
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:45,640
Eat well, sleep well.

602
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:48,720
Even if the sky falls,
you must keep on living.

603
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:59,200
Oh, heavens.

604
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,320
Who the hell left a laptop
out here in the woods?

605
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:08,400
All-New, go press something.

606
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:09,080
Yeah, go press it.

607
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:09,760
You're good at this.

608
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:10,760
Yeah.

609
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:15,520
Ear, Rock, Bear, Rock CHALLENGE.

610
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:22,160
Mushroom, Mushroom, Bear,
Ear, Rock, Ear, Rock, Bear.

611
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:27,040
Ear, Mushroom, Ear, Rock,
Rock, Bear, Bear, Rock.

612
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:32,680
Spear, Bear, Rock, Bear,
Ear, Mushroom, Bear, Rock.

613
00:28:34,040 --> 00:28:36,720
* * * * * *

614
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:37,760
What the hell?

615
00:28:37,760 --> 00:28:39,360
Can you just say whatever you want?

616
00:28:39,360 --> 00:28:42,400
Dog, Spear, Mushroom, Rock,
Dog, Ear, Rock, Bear.

617
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:44,560
Whoa! Sixteen characters, holy shit!

618
00:28:44,560 --> 00:28:47,680
Ear, Rock, Ear, Dog,
Bear, Ear, Dog, Bear.

619
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:51,360
Ear, Dog, Bear,
Pig, Bear, Dog.

620
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:53,040
Should I just kick this thing?

621
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:54,880
You're an absolute piece of trash!

622
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:55,840
Whose laptop is this anyway?

623
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:56,840
Is it yours, Gift?

624
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:57,800
Why the hell would I bring it here?

625
00:28:57,960 --> 00:29:00,000
Why is my line the longest one?
I really want to know.

626
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,760
Who on earth put this here?

627
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:03,960
Is it Ms. Petchgam Ploy's?
I wonder.

628
00:29:04,160 --> 00:29:04,960
She's been gone for a while.

629
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:09,640
When are you gonna say your line?

630
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:10,520
I already said it.

631
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:11,600
You say, let's go find some fish...

632
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:12,160
Oh, is it my turn?

633
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,160
Yes.

634
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:15,160
I'm sorry, I missed that.

635
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:16,760
Excuse me.

636
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:19,120
I'm not doing this anymore.

637
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:20,120
What?

638
00:29:20,120 --> 00:29:21,040
I'm gonna sleep.

639
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:22,560
But she's the Purser.

640
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:28,040
Hey!

641
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:30,160
She's sleeping now.

642
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:31,040
She's already sleeping.

643
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:31,800
Wait, what?

644
00:29:31,800 --> 00:29:32,400
Yeah, she's definitely sleeping now.

645
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:35,360
Oh, I'm already dead.

646
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:36,760
Mr. Bear.

647
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:38,960
I'm already dead here.

648
00:29:38,960 --> 00:29:40,960
I'm hurt! And I'm dead.

649
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:46,840
I'm already dead here.

650
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:50,240
I used to wonder...that the person who gave birth to me...

651
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:51,880
might actually be a tree...

652
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:53,320
Or maybe a rock?

653
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:54,440
That is correct.

654
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:56,880
There are still many things in this world that you might have never known before.

655
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:58,400
In that case, are you ready to embark on the journey?

656
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:00,760
If you're ready, let's go together with...

657
00:30:01,440 --> 00:30:03,720
the Navigator! Let's go!

658
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:09,520
A chopper is coming to pick us up and take us home!

659
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:15,040
Really?

660
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:17,120
And who did you contact to pick us up, Ms. Chaba?

661
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:17,960
Doctor Yab.

662
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:19,280
Doctor Yab!

663
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:20,640
One more time, please.

664
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:21,800
It's Doctor Yep.

665
00:30:21,800 --> 00:30:22,520
Doctor Yep!

666
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:23,720
It's Doctor Yep, sweetie.

667
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:25,640
Doctor Yep...

668
00:30:25,640 --> 00:30:27,880
Tik, can you turn to the camera a bit, please?

669
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:29,320
Turn to the camera?

670
00:30:29,320 --> 00:30:30,760
Don't get in the shot, Chaba!

671
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:31,880
A bit...

672
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:32,960
Is this enough of me showing up?

673
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:34,360
That works!

674
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:35,920
Oh, I got a crick in my neck.

675
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:38,480
Ready to embark on the journal...

676
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:39,360
The journey!

677
00:30:39,360 --> 00:30:40,600
Oh god, every single take...

678
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:41,600
Let's go, Tik.

679
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:44,680
Wait, do I need to repeat that "journal" line?

680
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:45,280
Yes, please.

681
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:46,680
Okay, we're keeping that, right?

682
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:47,480
Yeah, we're keeping it.

683
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:47,960
I love it.

684
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:51,960
Well, I’m going back to do the live stream for the...

685
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:53,920
Well, I’m going back to do the live stream...

686
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:55,800
Well, I’m going back...

687
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:58,520
Well, I’m going back to do the live stream...

688
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:02,520
Well, I’m going back to do the live stream for the 7/7 years...

689
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:04,680
What sale was it again?

690
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:07,240
The 7/7 mega sale. Okay.

691
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:08,760
I want to go home so bad!

692
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:11,080
Why don't we play a little game to open up to each other?

693
00:31:11,080 --> 00:31:13,000
Yay!

694
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:14,920
We can just come up with the questions ourselves.

695
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:15,960
Who wants to start first?

696
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:18,960
Have you guys...ever had a secret crush on a coworker?

697
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:21,800
Come here, let me do it for you.

698
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:23,200
Thank you.

699
00:31:23,200 --> 00:31:25,120
I’ve never felt this happy before.

700
00:31:25,120 --> 00:31:27,360
Chai, I'm cold.

701
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:31,760
Once we go back...will things be weird between us?

702
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:37,200
Glamorous Airline is here to take everyone back home!
